cast.text:
Day 119 of asking /matcha to support limit orders on /base 

When /matcha's shiny new ‚ÄúMarket Order Protocol‚Äù (Bids MightClear) struts into the DEX, YES2Crypto (Sheriff Hoody) - the OG liquidity wrangler - gets shelved. 

‚ÄúTo Base and beyond? More like to my roadmap‚Äôs trash bin,‚Äù mocks Bids, flashing LED wings labeled ‚ÄúLowest Fees EVER!‚Äù 

But when a Rug Pull Sid (a chaotic MEV bot) kidnaps /matcha‚Äôs codebase, YES2Crypto rallies the forgotten traders:

‚ÄúYOU ARE A protocol! Act like one!‚Äù

"You are a sad, strange little dev, and you have my liquidity" counters Bids MightClear, adding "Besides, we have the lowest fees."

YES2Crypto taunts "That wasn't lowest fees! That was slippage... with marketing!"

They reconcile, defeat Sid and sing "You've Got a Trend in Me"

text:
Yes, Warpcast is looking good, that's not debatable.

But let's not forget that X is paying out from income (ad payments) not a temporary marketing budget.

That's a huge difference when evaluating on revenue potential alone. There are plenty of reasons to love Farcaster, but Warpcast Rewards /= sustainable income. That narrative will only result in resentment later on when it dilutes out and dries up.

Come for the rewards, stay for the __________.

Gotta solve for that before the churn comes around again.

Frames is a good potential answer, but we're a ways out from monetizing frames to a level that can compete w/ web2 ad revenue.

text: I'm refactoring @warpee.eth today to prepare for adding workflow routing so it can start to answer different types of questions.  Making it more modular so it will be easier and safer to make future changes.  Deleting unused code. I'm also not happy with the results from the current prompt, and I keep making small tweaks which only gives worse replies.

Building an AI bot in public (updates cont.)

‚úÖRudimentary workflow routing is complete.
When you tag the bot and ask it a question, it now figures out whether it should look at transcripts or metadata to answer it. 
Example: "tell me about farcade" will search through transcripts and "tell me when chuckstock was on the show" will search through metadata.

Roadmap:
- Add a new workflow path to answer questions like "what were the highlights from the episode with chuckstock".  For this question, the bot needs to get the full transcript from a specific episode, instead of just searching through all transcripts or just metadata.
- Improve conversation ability.  Bot has rudimentary capability to have thread awareness but I learned there's a better way to handle this than prompt injection (https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/chat/create) 
- Create an additional database of all casts ever mentioned on our show 

What else would you like to see it do?

And I also want to start building a V2 frame

cast.text:
I just shipped an update to our /gmfarcaster AI bot to give it the ability to search through metadata about our show.

Previously it only had access to search through transcripts.

If you asked it questions like:

"when was the last time Dan was on the show?"
"how many episodes of The Hub have been recorded?"
"when was the first GM Farcaster episode?

It faltered because it would search transcripts for those answers and unless we actually answered that question on-air, it wouldn't be able to give an answer.

I got it working locally, shall we give it a try to see how it behaves here? ü§û ü§û
